<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-08-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-08-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="33" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d33">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName>, chargé, to
                            Mr. <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 34.]</seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-08-01"><hi rend="italic">August 1, 1894</hi></date>.
                            (Received August 2.)</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>War is declared. Japanese chargé d’affaires left Peking to-day. Has placed
                        interests [of] Japanese subjects in charge of legation of the United States.
                        Outbreak feared [at] Tientsin. Request war vessel.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Denby.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>